commit_message:
Rework NODE_CREATE action logic

This patch tunes the NODE_CREATE logic so that:

1. cluster desired capacity is adjusted based on its current capacity;
2. size checking failure will prevent the node from claiming itself a
   member of the cluster;
3. cluster status always gets updated provided that the engine tried to
   create the physical node;
4. cluster status is re-evaluated when appropriate based on its current
   member status.

